parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Airbag System Failure - Passenger Seat Sensor Mat Defect
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the passenger seat sensor mat can cause the airbag warning light to illuminate, indicating a potential safety risk. In the event of an accident, the airbags may not deploy, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: Airbag warning light illuminates
faulty sensor in the front passenger seat
code B1448 OCS Mat Defective
airbag light stays on even when there is no passenger in the seat.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Airbag Failure to Deploy in Accidents
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbags to deploy in accidents can result in serious injury or fatality.
symptoms: Airbags did not deploy in accidents
injuries sustained due to airbag failure
police reports filed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to accidents or near-misses, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floorboard
the vehicle decelerates without warning
the vehicle surges forward after braking
the rear brakes lock up
and smoke pours out from the rear tires.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to accidents or near-misses, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The front and rear brakes and calipers fail
the brake line hose is damaged
the vehicle decelerates without warning
the rear brakes lock up
and smoke pours out from the rear tires.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The interference between the accelerator and brake pedals can cause unintended acceleration, leading to accidents or near-misses, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal is depressed when the brake pedal is pressed
the vehicle surges forward after braking
and the brake pedal feels soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of fuel tank straps can cause the straps to fracture, leading to the fuel tank falling off the vehicle, which can result in accidents, fires, and explosions.
symptoms: Gas tank straps are excessively corroded
fractured
or broken
causing a scraping or dragging noise
and potentially leading to the fuel tank falling off the vehicle.
